text: Alright  I don t support underage drinking  but I know it s rampant at least in the U S  so I m here to make a quick PSA about safe drinking habits     PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE do not rail drinks  your body can only process so much alcohol  and that equals out to roughly  per type  not total    fl oz  of beer  closer to   if it s from a local brewery    fl oz  of wine  or  at the very most  two shots per hour  any more than this can cause you to lose feeling and result in severe injury or death  not directly  but not being able to feel pain doesn t help impaired judgment or avoiding danger    For beer or wine  try to drink the same amount of water as alcohol at a minimum  and with shots  at the very least    times as much water  as this helps to dilute and re hydrate the body  it also helps to prevent horrible hangovers the morning after    If a friend is drinking heavily  stay with them  it may seem OK to leave them with a blanket and pillow next to a toilet  but this can and has turned out very poorly for countless people  often resulting in permanent brain damage due to oxygen deprivation due to choking on their own vomit  or from seizures caused by the alcohol  you don t need to have a history of seizures to have one while drinking  so stay with them  even if you don t want to  or make sure that they have someone to check on them every few minutes  Drink as little as possible  period end of story  drinking as much as possible may seem cool  but it just turns you into a belligerent dumbass  don t do it Stay safe peeps  and please  make good decisions amp x B amp x B amp x B you don t have to listen to me  but it would be a lot cooler if you did
summary: Don't drink too much alcohol. Drink as little as possible. Don't leave a drunk friend with a blanket and pillow next to the toilet. Drink the same amount of water as alcohol for beer and shots for wine. Stay with your friends who are drinking.
